{"title": "Story of the Atlantic Telegraph", "description": "Cyrus W. Field had a dream: to link the Old World of Britain and Europe to that of the New World of North America by a telegraph cable stretching across the great Atlantic Ocean. It took him thirteen years, a lot of money, and many men and ships and cable to make it happen. He wanted to bring the world together and make it a smaller place; to forge alliances and achieve peace. This is his story. (Introduction by Alex C. Telander)", "duration": 34243, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2524", "name": "Henry M. Field"}], "coverArt": "http://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt13/StoryAtlanticTelegraph_1201.jpg", "copyright_year": "1866", "genres": ["*Non-fiction", "History", "Technology & Engineering"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Alex C. Telander"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Alex C. Telander"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Availle"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Guero"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [2368], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/story_atlantic_telegraph_at_librivox/storyatlantictelegraph_00_field_64kb.mp3", "duration": 264}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I", "readers": [2368], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/story_atlantic_telegraph_at_librivox/storyatlantictelegraph_01_field_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1242}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter II", "readers": [2368], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/story_atlantic_telegraph_at_librivox/storyatlantictelegraph_02_field_64kb.mp3", "duration": 765}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter III", "readers": [2368], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/story_atlantic_telegraph_at_librivox/storyatlantictelegraph_03_field_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1143}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter IV", "readers": [2368], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/story_atlantic_telegraph_at_librivox/storyatlantictelegraph_04_field_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1026}, {"s